Grupo Suramericana to Expand Abroad, Bernal Tells La Republica

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-06-07T13:14:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/grupo-suramericana-to-expand-abroad-bernal-tells-la-republica.html
Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR) ,
the parent company of  Colombia ’s largest bank, plans to expand
abroad and increase revenue from overseas to at least 50 percent
of the company’s total within five to 10 years, the company’s
Chief Financial Officer Andres Bernal said in an  interview  with
La Republica daily.  The Medellin-based holding company currently gets between
15 percent and 20 percent of its revenue from abroad, Bernal
told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  